Program: Discovery
Title: Sickle-cell disease in Ghana
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx4c
Last Broadcast Date: 07 May 1998
Report from a children's ward in Ghana and sickle-cell disease. A new vaccine could help protect children from the disease, which is prevalent in 2 per cent of Ghanaians. Also why eggshells among some breeds of European birds are getting thinner. Presenter: Graham Easton.